	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just want to say how much this spell has grown on me. At first, you see it and you think "oh wow. A 5 point damage shield. Whoopty-doo". Well, I was in a group and things were going very well so I decided to experiment with some spells I never really used very often. One was O'Keils flickering flame. There was a druid and a mage already DSing in the group, so that was covered, but I felt like trying it anyway. My roomate has a computer and was playing a tank in the group too, so I could see the computer screen. To my surprise, I cast O'Keils on her, and it stuck...on top of the druid and mage ds. All of the sudden that ds was doing about 30 points of damage every time they were hit. That adds up. The 10 points of FR is nice also. It just saved her from some nasty AoE spells we had dropped on us. In a group with other DS'ers, O'Keils rocks. By itself it isn't anything to shout about, but when you can bump that stronger DS up 5 points, that makes a significant difference. Plus, it lasts longer than those other DS's so you don't constantly have to redo it. Just my support for a very underated spell in the game IMO.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
