	   <tr><td colspan=2>With the right types of INT adding equipment, the right spawn, and the ever so helpful SoW/Jboots you can just about level yourself well into the 50s without ever having to group. Start off the bat, in whatever zone your race starts in. Then in the early teens head off to NRo and kite spiders and scarabs. Head to Oasis for the late teens and early 20s. For the 20s you can pretty much stay in Ill Omen. In the 30s, depending on your faction, you can either find yourself a bard spawn to take, head to the Ocean of Tears and camp some Sisters, or just go to South Karan and kite some aviaks or Splitpaw Gnolls. Late 30s you can always camp the Millers in Qeynos Hills for some nice exp. Afterwards heading over to Eastern Wastes and kiting some kodiaks or wolves near the bridge to Iceclad in case you need to sprint away from death if you go short of mana. And in your low - mid 40s you can always do like everyone else and camp the unholy hell out of the Bloodgills in Ill Omen with a little strategy, enduring breath (if you ya need it), and levitate until level 50. Whoever told you, you need to group was full of it. You dont! If you like grouping rather then soloing then by all means group to your heart's delight. There's my 2 cents worth. Adios<br><br><br>Simethos Teirstorm<br>Teir'dal Wizard <br>Familjen<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
